 Decode String 

Problem Statement

Given an encoded string, return its decoded form.

Encoding rule: k[encoded_string] â†’ repeat the string inside brackets k times.

Example:

Input: "3[a2[c]]"

Output: "accaccacc"





ğŸ§  Approach

Use a stack to process characters.

For each character:

If not ] â†’ push into stack.

If ] â†’

1. Pop characters until [ to form substring.


2. Pop digits to get repeat count k.


3. Push back k * substring.




Finally, join all stack items into the decoded string.



        

â± Complexity

Time: O(n) â†’ each char processed at most twice (push + pop).

Space: O(n) â†’ stack holds characters and substrings.


